When creating an issue through a direct html link: [http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Creating+Issues+via+direct+HTML+links] and using the &decorator=popup parameter (referring to atlassian-jira/decorators/popups.jsp) upon error the parameter &decorator=popup is removed and the user is redirected to secure/CreateIssueDetails.jspa

h4. To reproduce:
* Edit the atlassian-jira/decorators/popups.jsp with something
Eg:
{code}
<div>
<img src="http://image.minoc.com/zd_images/2012/22/lol_face.jpg">
</div>   
{code}
* Figure out direct link (ie: project id, issuetype, componenet, and "&decorator=popup")
Eg:
{code}
http://JIRA:8505/secure/CreateIssueDetails!init.jspa?pid=10000&issuetype=1&components=10000&decorator=popup
{code}
* Go to the direct issue create link
* Don't fill any mandatory fields
* Click submit
* Note that the page redirects to:
{code}
http://JIRA:8505/secure/CreateIssueDetails.jspa
{code}

It would be best if this could redirect back to its self by default and not elsewhere.

